  "content:encoded": "\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Reuters was <a href=\"https://app.assets.reuters.com/e/er?utm_campaign=Reuters%20Best%20Weekly_NWSLTR_NEW_GLOB_B2B_2201&utm_medium=email&utm_source=Eloqua&utm_content=B2B%20220915%20NEWS%20GLOB%20REUTERS%20BEST%20AWARE%20NWSLTR%20WEEKLY&s=2124157686&lid=29098&elqTrackId=896B0F00C100091389D509BDD82E2CC8&elq=ed82dc55952f46299f06302cd4bbe4d1&elqaid=2354&elqat=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">first to report </a>Colombia&#8217;s state-run oil company Ecopetrol has asked the oil regulator to suspend contracts for two fracking pilot projects for 90 days. The two projects — being developed in Santander province by Ecopetrol and U.S. oil major Exxon Mobil Corp — have faced stiff resistance from environmental groups and could be halted outright if a law, backed by the administration of new leftist President Gustavo Petro, passes congress.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.reutersagency.com/en/reutersbest/article/reuters-reveals-colombias-ecopetrol-asks-to-suspend-fracking-contracts-for-90-days/\">Reuters reveals Colombia&#8217;s Ecopetrol asks to suspend fracking contracts for 90 days</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.reutersagency.com/en/\">Reuters News Agency</a>.</p>\n"
